          <tr><td><strong>Kennedy Memorial Drive</strong></td><td>Shopping corridor</td><td>$10-13</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Elm Street</strong></td><td>Historic district</td><td>$11-14</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The opportunity:</strong> Central Maine's largest city with only 2-3 competitors. The Colby investment is real and bringing a new demographic.</li>
        <li><strong>Colby matters:</strong> Faculty, students, and event attendees bring cannabis experience and disposable income. They expect quality, not bargain products.</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery play:</strong> Central Maine has a dispensary access problem. Skowhegan, Somerset County, northern Kennebec County — all underserved. A Waterville delivery operation can capture regional customers.</li>
        <li><strong>Not Portland:</strong> Don't expect Portland numbers. But the competition is thinner and a well-run store can establish dominance in the region.</li>
        <li><strong>Investment:</strong> $250K-$350K is realistic. Lower rent than Portland, lower competition, lower ceiling.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

